Issues.Body:
This PR makes utility classes use variables with fallbacks for their underlying values, rather than just using the bare value:

```css
/* Before */
.pt-4 {
  padding-top: 1rem;
}

/* After */
.pt-4 {
  padding-top: var(--spacing-4, 1rem);
}
```

Not totally sold on it yet but opening as a draft as a reminder to discuss with the team next week.

### v4.0.0-alpha.6

Crashes if `.scss` file used:
```scss
@import "tailwindcss";
```
![image](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/assets/109352196/99572b8a-a184-42b5-a522-2421df6ea5d9)

![Screenshot_7-3-2024_213151_localhost](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/assets/153141620/e850f241-c879-4c8a-9448-dc306463f99c)
![image](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/assets/153141620/e184f37d-71e4-4b0f-82be-a48bcdd24a75)

body {
  @apply bg-black min-h-full w-full ;
}

This PR makes sure that `@apply` doesn't error when there is extra leading or trailing whitespace:

```css
.foo {
  @apply  flex  ;
}
```

Fixes #13134.
